  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Genetic polymorphism affects plasma concentration of antiretroviral therapy in HIV patients.
      The investigators investigate the prevalence of genetic polymorphism affecting efavirenz
      metabolism and the corresponding pharmacokinetics of different genotypes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Eligible patients are invited to donate blood samples for pharmacokinetic study and genotype
      analysis
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
